  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "- https://www.ethernodes.org says 7% of the network is using Erigon\r\n- The [wiki page for transition](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/wiki/Criteria-for-transitioning-from-Alpha-to-Beta) is unclear if the goals are achieved already. Perhaps you could create a GitHub Project, or use Milestones, or something, to signify what's left to be done for Beta?\r\n- It's very tiring to have Erigon breaking and corrupting data release after release\r\n\r\nIt would be great if some focus was poured on getting a stable release out, a release that won't corrupt data & won't need \"updates\" (besides security) for at least 6 months.",
